choices.text:
There are three killers in a room. Someone enters the room and kills one of them. Nobody leaves the room. How many killers are left in the room?
After someone kills one of the killers, there would be two remaining killers in the room. So when you say "nobody leaves the room", it means that all three people (the original three killers) are still in the room and only one has been killed by the newcomer.
